<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="149" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[175,1004,1035,1215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="MHNP" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
This taxon was described from a single specimen collected in «Caroline». The 
<typeStatus box="[175,261,1061,1082]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">holotype</typeStatus>
, a female in 
<collectionCode box="[397,468,1061,1082]" country="France" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/a5xg-x4h4" name="Museum d'Histoire Naturelle Perpignan" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">MHNP</collectionCode>
, is labelled «[illegible letters on a small green label]/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Caroline C. Reiche" box="[175,450,1088,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvulus">parvulus Caroline C. Reiche</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]/Muséum Paris [handwritten]»
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[175,1004,1035,1215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
The 
<typeStatus box="[242,325,1114,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">holotype</typeStatus>
(SBL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[386,404,1115,1135]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">¼</emphasis>
<quantity box="[408,484,1114,1135]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7 mm</quantity>
; ABL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,562,1115,1135]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">¼</emphasis>
about 
<quantity box="[625,699,1114,1135]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
) belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" box="[850,902,1114,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[850,902,1114,1135]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and is conspecific with specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Allen, 1972" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[525,770,1141,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aduncus">
<emphasis box="[525,636,1141,1162]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">L. aduncus</emphasis>
Allen, 1972
</taxonomicName>
[NEW SYNONYMY]. The relatively large size (ABL: 
<quantity box="[467,548,1167,1188]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[560,576,1168,1188]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">þ</emphasis>
) and the shape of the pronotum enable identification of this species.
</paragraph>
